    {
      "id": "abe7fa45-8e33-488f-8e24-680247d521e0",
      "name": "Understand & Observe",
      "itemLimit": 5,
      "stateMappings": {
        "Product Backlog Item": "Approved",
        "Bug": "Approved"
      },
      "isSplit": false,
      "description": "We want to learn more about\nthe potential user, his/her needs, and the tasks that he/she must\ncomplete. For the\ndefinition of the design challenge, we use \"WHY\"\nand \"HOW\" questions in order to broaden or limit the scope. Only reality can show whether our assumptions will be confirmed. When possible we should speak to potential users in order to learn more about their needs, and ask open questions to test our own assumptions.",
      "columnType": "inProgress"
    },
    {
      "id": "7bdcfe06-29ac-4edf-b686-fb2f970ae664",
      "name": "Define",
      "itemLimit": 5,
      "stateMappings": {
        "Product Backlog Item": "Approved",
        "Bug": "Approved"
      },
      "isSplit": false,
      "description": "In this phase, we focus on evaluating, interpreting, and weighting\nthe findings we have gathered. The\npoint of view is usually formulated as a sentence ( \"How might\nwe..”).",
      "columnType": "inProgress"
    },
    {
      "id": "8a521cbb-57b2-4498-8796-741275fae0bc",
      "name": "Ideate",
      "itemLimit": 5,
      "stateMappings": {
        "Product Backlog Item": "Approved",
        "Bug": "Approved"
      },
      "isSplit": false,
      "description": "Ideation is a step toward finding solutions for\nour problem. Usually, different forms of brainstorming and specific creativity techniques..\n",
      "columnType": "inProgress"
    },
    {
      "id": "d1c7670f-3587-45e2-ac3f-473e3c6e77a4",
      "name": "Prototype",
      "itemLimit": 5,
      "stateMappings": {
        "Product Backlog Item": "Committed",
        "Bug": "Committed"
      },
      "isSplit": false,
      "description": "The building of prototypes helps us to test our ideas or solutions,\nquickly and without risk, with our potential users. In particular,\ndigital solutions can be prototyped with simple paper models\nor mock-ups. Prototypes range from critical experience prototypes all the way\nto a final prototype. ",
      "columnType": "inProgress"
    },
    {
      "id": "9b8ddf95-c99a-4ffa-9eeb-10d50b0826c8",
      "name": "Test",
      "itemLimit": 5,
      "stateMappings": {
        "Product Backlog Item": "Approved",
        "Bug": "Committed"
      },
      "isSplit": false,
      "description": "When testing, the most important thing is that interaction with\nthe potential user takes place and that we document the results.\nThe tests\nprovide us with feedback that helps with the improvement of\nour prototypes. We should learn from these ideas and develop\nthem further until we completely convince the users of the idea.",
      "columnType": "inProgress"
    },
    {
